text: I'm planning to do primary research on our customer pain points. Wanted to know where to start when you want to establish a cadence for feedback calls with customers. Do I go through sales or pre-sales? Do I have to establish a rapo first? Any off the cuff real-world tips on how to approach this? Any advice would be much appreciated

Do I go through sales or pre-sales? Do I have to establish a rapo first? Any off the cuff real-world tips on how to approach this? Any advice would be much appreciated

text:
Depends on whose influence you can leverage for buy in. 

This varies by org size - but it'd be better to cozy up to CS folks than pre sales if you plan to keep up the primary research for the long haul. 

This also helps in making a stronger case to customers you're reaching out to (because CSRs keeps in touch with them constantly, they'd trust a familiar face more) 

CS for execution, whoever's in-charge of them for buy-in imo. 

More on that 

Drawing out good arguments on what they stand to lose if you don't have these customer insights should work. 

Bet on --

opportunity cost + how it helps drive the north star metric + low-touch execution plan that doesn't bother too many parties

-- to get the green light
